th one of the three aspects - seismic, nuclear and medical - of the drama as it unfolded. For each of these components, objects of the three parts of this report, the analysis of observed events in Fukushima was supplemented by a reflection o the strengths and weaknesses of these areas in France, in order to formulate the necessary recommendations and to answer scientific and societal question public arises. Although uncertainties remain and that new information still come each month to enrich the record, the enclosed reports seemed complete enough to be published in the state, after the anniversary of this tragedy that will long continue to challenge us.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 4aNuclear. 7aSCIENCE / Physics / Nuclear.2bisacsh1 aBrézin, Édouard, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aFriedel, Jacques, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEDP Sciences Backlist eBook Package 2001 - 2015z97831107564180 cprintz978275980755040uhttps://doi.org/10.1051/978-2-7598-2486-1zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9782759824861zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9782759824861/original  a978-3-11-075641-8 EDP Sciences Backlist eBook Package 2001 - 2015c2001d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA